# Build Instructions

<!-- Commands acecode can use to build, run, and test the project. -->
```bash
# Build
cmake -S . -B build -G Ninja -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
cmake --build build

# Test
cmake --build build --target unit_tests
ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure
```

# Architecture

<!-- Top-level modules, data flow, external services. Keep under 300 lines so this file
     stays cheap to inject into the system prompt every turn. -->
- `src/` — production code
- `tests/` — unit tests (globbed automatically by `tests/CMakeLists.txt`)
- `docs/` — contributor docs

# Conventions

<!-- Coding style, PR conventions, anything agent-facing that isn't obvious from the code. -->
- Use `Edit` / `Read` tools over `bash cat`/`sed`.
- Commit messages: imperative mood, present tense, ≤70-char subject.
- When touching tests: every TEST body gets a Chinese comment explaining the scenario.

